1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:04,045
- [distant gunfire]
- [girl screaming, crying]

2
00:00:04,129 --> 00:00:06,881
[grunting]

3
00:00:06,965 --> 00:00:08,758
[gasping]

4
00:00:09,342 --> 00:00:12,429
[girl crying]

5
00:00:12,512 --> 00:00:14,180
[Jalil shouting]

6
00:00:14,848 --> 00:00:17,350
- [woman] <i>Mama!</i>
- [yelling]

7
00:00:17,434 --> 00:00:21,020
We will not give up.
We will return to Manila.

8
00:00:21,855 --> 00:00:23,148
[Marcus] <i>You'll go home to your family!</i>

9
00:00:23,231 --> 00:00:25,942
- [ominous music playing]
- [gunshots blasting]

10
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:30,572
[grunting]

11
00:00:31,781 --> 00:00:34,659
[grunting and groaning]

12
00:00:38,621 --> 00:00:39,998
[ominous music continues]

13
00:00:42,876 --> 00:00:46,796
[grunting]

14
00:00:55,930 --> 00:00:58,016
[mysterious theme music playing]

15
00:01:15,408 --> 00:01:17,077
[gunshots blasting]

16
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:22,332
[siren wailing]

17
00:01:25,794 --> 00:01:27,253
‪POLICE

18
00:01:30,465 --> 00:01:37,430
[grim music playing]

19
00:01:42,852 --> 00:01:44,813
[Marcus] <i>This isn't an isolated incident.</i>

20
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:46,773
- [reporter 1] <i>Walking down an alley…</i>
- [reporter 2] <i>Seized from them…</i>

21
00:01:46,856 --> 00:01:48,191
[reporter 3]
<i>The driver crashed into a car…</i>

22
00:01:48,274 --> 00:01:50,276
[Marcus] <i>And this isn't just</i>
<i>a simple crime.</i>

23
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:52,487
<i>This is the result</i>
<i>of the widespread proliferation</i>

24
00:01:52,570 --> 00:01:54,197
<i>of firearms in the country.</i>

25
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:58,576
<i>They're smuggled in,</i>
<i>distributed, and sold.</i>

26
00:01:58,660 --> 00:02:01,037
<i>Until they end up in just anyone's hands.</i>

27
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:02,956
<i>It's hard to stop.</i>

28
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:05,208
<i>Because there are those who benefit.</i>

29
00:02:05,291 --> 00:02:07,127
<i>There are those who protect it.</i>

30
00:02:07,919 --> 00:02:10,922
<i>Powerful people who don't want it to end.</i>

31
00:02:11,005 --> 00:02:12,382
<i>If this isn't stopped,</i>

32
00:02:12,966 --> 00:02:16,636
<i>in an instant, anyone's life can change.</i>

33
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:19,722
[grim music playing]

34
00:02:21,558 --> 00:02:24,894
[grim music continues]

35
00:02:28,982 --> 00:02:31,359
<i>Parents burying their children.</i>

36
00:02:39,993 --> 00:02:44,664
[grim music continues]

37
00:02:46,207 --> 00:02:49,419
<i>And children losing</i>
<i>their parents too soon.</i>

38
00:02:58,094 --> 00:03:02,891
[pensive music playing]

39
00:03:03,933 --> 00:03:04,767
[Lara] Confirmed.

40
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:07,770
The serial numbers of the firearms
we retrieved are confirmed.

41
00:03:07,854 --> 00:03:11,482
They're part of the batch
of illegally smuggled firearms

42
00:03:11,566 --> 00:03:12,859
brought into the country.

43
00:03:14,277 --> 00:03:16,404
These illegal firearms…

44
00:03:18,615 --> 00:03:21,075
They're ending up everywhere,
completely out of control.

45
00:03:21,159 --> 00:03:22,577
You're right.

46
00:03:23,244 --> 00:03:25,955
That's why gun-related violence
and crime keep rising.

47
00:03:27,206 --> 00:03:29,417
This is an epidemic we need to stop.

48
00:03:30,835 --> 00:03:32,170
But the question is…

49
00:03:33,504 --> 00:03:35,465
where are these illegal firearms…

50
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:38,509
…really being distributed?

51
00:03:41,304 --> 00:03:45,767
[pensive music continues]

52
00:03:58,404 --> 00:04:05,203
[overlapping clamor]

53
00:04:07,455 --> 00:04:09,290
[indistinct chattering]

54
00:04:09,374 --> 00:04:11,459
9,500 is too expensive. Make it 7,000!

55
00:04:11,542 --> 00:04:14,796
Come on, I'm losing money at that price!

56
00:04:14,879 --> 00:04:16,547
[dark music playing]

57
00:04:24,764 --> 00:04:26,391
[grunting]

58
00:04:32,897 --> 00:04:36,734
[dark music continues]

59
00:04:45,493 --> 00:04:46,953
Don't sell to my rival.

60
00:04:47,036 --> 00:04:48,079
This is business.

61
00:04:48,162 --> 00:04:50,498
Next shipment, buy in bulk,
so you don't get beaten to it.

62
00:04:53,918 --> 00:04:56,462
Peklat! Can I get some money for food?

63
00:04:58,172 --> 00:04:59,132
You're so stingy!

64
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:04,387
[dark music continues]

65
00:05:13,021 --> 00:05:15,064
- [Marcus] All units set.
- [beeps]

66
00:05:17,191 --> 00:05:22,947
[ominous music playing]

67
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:36,961
Three o'clock, west.
Twelve o'clock, north.

68
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:38,796
Two o'clock, northeast.

69
00:05:43,259 --> 00:05:45,011
- Could you please double-check?
- [man] Copy, ma'am.

70
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:53,478
[ominous music continues]

71
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:58,816
- [Marcus] Visuals clear.
- [system beeping]

72
00:05:59,984 --> 00:06:01,611
Civilians heavy.

73
00:06:02,195 --> 00:06:03,279
I see you.

74
00:06:04,989 --> 00:06:09,285
[ominous music continues]

75
00:06:10,995 --> 00:06:12,497
- [clicking]
- [beeping]

76
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:14,165
[overlapping clamor]

77
00:06:17,627 --> 00:06:21,255
[ominous music continues]

78
00:06:26,260 --> 00:06:30,223
[clicking]

79
00:06:31,557 --> 00:06:33,142
‪[beeping]

80
00:06:35,853 --> 00:06:37,647
[man] Boss! Boss, got more?

81
00:06:41,526 --> 00:06:46,239
[ominous music continues]

82
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:55,998
[clicking]

83
00:06:58,167 --> 00:07:02,296
[ominous music continues]

84
00:07:11,764 --> 00:07:13,099
You got pompano?

85
00:07:13,683 --> 00:07:19,272
[tense music playing]

86
00:07:20,815 --> 00:07:22,024
You alone?

87
00:07:28,906 --> 00:07:30,199
Plenty.

88
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:32,869
[clicking]

89
00:07:44,714 --> 00:07:48,843
[tense music continues]

90
00:07:49,886 --> 00:07:51,971
Agent Reyes, confirm shipment.

91
00:07:55,558 --> 00:07:57,852
[Marcus] AK, Russian-made.

92
00:07:58,769 --> 00:08:00,396
M16?

93
00:08:03,441 --> 00:08:04,609
Good.

94
00:08:05,109 --> 00:08:06,944
[distortion]

95
00:08:07,028 --> 00:08:08,654
Marcus, come again?

96
00:08:08,738 --> 00:08:09,739
[suspenseful music]

97
00:08:09,822 --> 00:08:10,740
[agent] Hurry.

98
00:08:10,823 --> 00:08:14,869
[tense music continues]

99
00:08:27,965 --> 00:08:28,925
I can't hear you.

100
00:08:30,051 --> 00:08:31,886
[Felix] Please repeat. Please repeat.

101
00:08:31,969 --> 00:08:36,015
[tense music continues]

102
00:08:36,891 --> 00:08:38,351
[dramatic bang]

103
00:08:38,434 --> 00:08:40,561
[whistle blowing]

104
00:08:44,065 --> 00:08:44,941
[distorted whirring]

105
00:08:45,024 --> 00:08:46,817
- [distorted whirring]
- Agent Reyes!

106
00:08:46,901 --> 00:08:48,277
Agent Reyes, status?

107
00:08:48,361 --> 00:08:49,695
[grunting]

108
00:08:52,490 --> 00:08:53,824
[man] Take him down!

109
00:08:55,576 --> 00:08:58,829
[suspenseful music playing]

110
00:09:08,339 --> 00:09:10,132
- [man grunts]
- [gunshots]

111
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:13,261
- [gunshots]
- [man grunts]

112
00:09:16,556 --> 00:09:18,641
[rapid gunfire]

113
00:09:19,559 --> 00:09:20,977
[Marcus grunting]

114
00:09:21,060 --> 00:09:22,353
[gunshots]

115
00:09:22,436 --> 00:09:27,316
[grunting and groaning]

116
00:09:35,074 --> 00:09:36,742
Run! Hurry! Get out of here!

117
00:09:36,826 --> 00:09:38,119
Hurry! Move!

118
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:47,044
[gunshots]

119
00:09:47,128 --> 00:09:50,715
- [man grunts]
- [suspenseful music continues]

120
00:09:51,549 --> 00:09:52,717
[grunting]

121
00:09:54,302 --> 00:09:55,928
[man grunts]

122
00:09:56,012 --> 00:09:58,931
[explosion]

123
00:09:59,015 --> 00:10:00,891
[man groans]

124
00:10:00,975 --> 00:10:02,643
- [gunfire]
- [suspenseful music continues]

125
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:08,357
[panting]

126
00:10:11,193 --> 00:10:13,613
- [overlapping clamor]
- [rapid gunfire]

127
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:26,834
[rapid gunfire]

128
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:37,678
[gun clicks]

129
00:10:38,429 --> 00:10:41,641
[suspenseful music continues]

130
00:11:02,286 --> 00:11:03,746
[rapid gunfire]

131
00:11:07,249 --> 00:11:09,001
You handle this. I'm out!

132
00:11:09,085 --> 00:11:11,170
Marcus, Peklat is escaping!

133
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:15,049
[rapid gunfire]

134
00:11:17,093 --> 00:11:18,844
[rapid gunfire]

135
00:11:25,893 --> 00:11:27,395
[grunting]

136
00:11:46,205 --> 00:11:48,707
- [man grunts]
- [woman crying]

137
00:11:52,962 --> 00:11:57,800
[suspenseful music continues]

138
00:12:01,262 --> 00:12:03,097
[engine revving]

139
00:12:04,515 --> 00:12:05,349
Marcus!

140
00:12:08,686 --> 00:12:10,604
[engine roaring]

141
00:12:12,148 --> 00:12:12,898
- [Marcus grunts]
- [man grunts]

142
00:12:16,235 --> 00:12:18,988
[tires screeching]

143
00:12:19,488 --> 00:12:21,073
[tense music continues]

144
00:12:24,285 --> 00:12:25,828
[brakes squealing]

145
00:12:29,999 --> 00:12:31,542
[tires screech]

146
00:12:34,086 --> 00:12:35,588
[engine revving]

147
00:12:36,755 --> 00:12:40,634
[tense music continues]

148
00:12:43,220 --> 00:12:46,140
[engine roaring]

149
00:12:46,223 --> 00:12:47,600
[heavy thud]

150
00:12:50,311 --> 00:12:52,021
[people clamoring]

151
00:12:52,813 --> 00:12:54,023
- Help!
- [boy] Badong!

152
00:12:54,106 --> 00:12:57,109
[Peklat] Come closer,
and I'll finish this one off!

153
00:12:57,193 --> 00:12:58,903
- [Badong crying]
- [Peklat breathing heavily]

154
00:12:58,986 --> 00:13:00,196
- I dare you!
- Brother.

155
00:13:00,279 --> 00:13:01,614
- [boy] Badong!
- I'll kill this little boy!

156
00:13:01,697 --> 00:13:03,741
- [woman] Badong!
- [sobs] Badong…

157
00:13:03,824 --> 00:13:04,950
[Badong sobbing] Brother…

158
00:13:05,034 --> 00:13:07,703
[Peklat] What? No one's safe anymore!

159
00:13:07,786 --> 00:13:09,663
- He's going to be dead!
- [exclaims] Brother!

160
00:13:09,747 --> 00:13:13,125
- [suspenseful music playing]
- [hurried footsteps]

161
00:13:13,959 --> 00:13:15,711
Please, help me!

162
00:13:15,794 --> 00:13:17,796
[tense music]

163
00:13:32,394 --> 00:13:33,562
[music intensifies]

164
00:13:33,646 --> 00:13:35,231
- [gunshots]
- [groans]

165
00:13:35,314 --> 00:13:36,857
- [flesh squelches]
- [knife clatters]

166
00:13:36,941 --> 00:13:38,776
[woman, boy sobbing]

167
00:13:38,859 --> 00:13:40,486
- [Badong sobs] Brother…
- [man shouts]

168
00:13:40,569 --> 00:13:44,198
- [morose music playing]
- [sobbing]

169
00:13:45,824 --> 00:13:46,867
‪[indistinct dialogue]

170
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:48,744
[all sobbing]

171
00:13:53,374 --> 00:13:55,000
[sobbing]

172
00:14:00,714 --> 00:14:03,008
[car engine revving]

173
00:14:05,010 --> 00:14:06,220
I wonder how Agent Reyes is holding up.

174
00:14:06,303 --> 00:14:07,555
He might need backup.

175
00:14:08,389 --> 00:14:09,765
[snickering]

176
00:14:09,848 --> 00:14:11,725
Of all people, you're doubting Marcus?

177
00:14:11,809 --> 00:14:13,811
Bad weeds never die, madam.

178
00:14:18,065 --> 00:14:19,900
[grunting]

179
00:14:19,984 --> 00:14:20,985
[man] In the car.

180
00:14:22,611 --> 00:14:24,530
- Agent Reyes, radio check.
- [radio crackles]

181
00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:26,198
[rear door slams shut]

182
00:14:26,282 --> 00:14:27,950
Agent Reyes, radio check.

183
00:14:28,033 --> 00:14:29,034
[static buzzing]

184
00:14:30,661 --> 00:14:34,081
[pensive music playing]

185
00:14:37,126 --> 00:14:38,919
- [Marcus] <i>Target secured.</i>
- [radio static]

186
00:14:44,508 --> 00:14:46,218
[boy] Thank you, mister.

187
00:14:47,636 --> 00:14:50,055
[mellow music playing]

188
00:15:10,618 --> 00:15:13,829
[mellow music continues]

189
00:15:22,254 --> 00:15:24,006
[men whooping, laughing]

190
00:15:24,089 --> 00:15:25,883
Sir Marcus!

191
00:15:26,383 --> 00:15:27,676
- You're the man.
- Whoo!

192
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:28,928
Congratulations.

193
00:15:29,428 --> 00:15:32,514
[indistinct chatter]

194
00:15:32,598 --> 00:15:34,767
- You're really one of a kind, Marcus.
- Yes.

195
00:15:35,351 --> 00:15:36,518
[man] Whoo!

196
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:37,937
Good job, Reyes.

197
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:39,313
[Marcus sighing]

198
00:15:39,396 --> 00:15:42,441
[mellow music continues]

199
00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:48,989
[drums begin playing]

200
00:15:53,035 --> 00:15:54,578
[reporter] <i>Just in.</i>

201
00:15:54,662 --> 00:15:56,956
<i>A notorious arms-smuggling syndicate</i>

202
00:15:57,039 --> 00:15:59,875
<i>has been taken down by members</i>
<i>of Task Force Alpha,</i>

203
00:15:59,959 --> 00:16:01,585
<i>a crime-fighting group</i>

204
00:16:01,669 --> 00:16:05,130
<i>composed of Special</i>
<i>Investigations Division agents</i>

205
00:16:05,214 --> 00:16:09,259
<i>and policemen from the National</i>
<i>Law Enforcement Agency.</i>

206
00:16:09,343 --> 00:16:10,970
<i>According to authorities,</i>

207
00:16:11,053 --> 00:16:13,973
<i>they had been monitoring</i>
<i>this syndicate for a long time.</i>

208
00:16:14,056 --> 00:16:16,725
<i>They said the group carried out</i>
<i>illegal arms transactions</i>

209
00:16:16,809 --> 00:16:18,769
<i>at fish ports</i>

210
00:16:18,852 --> 00:16:21,939
<i>and smuggling contraband</i>
<i>hidden among fish shipments</i>

211
00:16:22,022 --> 00:16:26,276
<i>worth between seven and nine million.</i>

212
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:28,654
NOTORIOUS ARMS-SMUGGLING SYNDICATE
APPREHENDED BY TASK FORCE ALPHA

213
00:16:28,737 --> 00:16:29,613
[stirring music playing]

214
00:16:30,948 --> 00:16:34,576
[people applauding, whooping]

215
00:16:43,544 --> 00:16:45,045
[applause dies down]

216
00:16:45,129 --> 00:16:47,214
Agent Lara Angeles.

217
00:16:48,215 --> 00:16:49,550
Congratulations!

218
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:54,638
You and your team never fail
to impress me.

219
00:16:57,558 --> 00:16:58,600
[footsteps approaching]

220
00:17:01,854 --> 00:17:03,856
Where is Agent Reyes?

221
00:17:03,939 --> 00:17:06,025
Oh, you know him, sir.

222
00:17:06,108 --> 00:17:08,152
He always make a stop after every mission.

223
00:17:08,235 --> 00:17:09,778
[somber music playing]

224
00:17:17,786 --> 00:17:19,455
Patient in Bed 1, monitor the BP.

225
00:17:19,538 --> 00:17:21,248
If it rises, administer labetalol.

226
00:17:21,331 --> 00:17:22,207
Noted, Doc.

227
00:17:22,291 --> 00:17:24,460
Doc, the patient in Bed 4 says the pain

228
00:17:24,543 --> 00:17:26,587
in their thigh is no longer
relieved by paracetamol.

229
00:17:26,670 --> 00:17:28,338
- Age?
- [resident 2] Female, 83.

230
00:17:28,422 --> 00:17:29,798
Give the patient Orphenadrine.

231
00:17:29,882 --> 00:17:32,301
Tell their guardian to apply
a hot compress.

232
00:17:32,384 --> 00:17:33,677
[resident 2] Okay. Noted, Doc.

233
00:17:36,346 --> 00:17:38,057
Doctor Teresa Reyes.

234
00:17:38,140 --> 00:17:39,266
[Marcus clears throat]

235
00:17:39,850 --> 00:17:42,728
Um, please register with the triage nurse

236
00:17:42,811 --> 00:17:44,271
so that we can take care of you.

237
00:17:44,354 --> 00:17:45,773
[dryly] Wow.

238
00:17:45,856 --> 00:17:48,358
Don't you recognize your son's voice?

239
00:17:48,442 --> 00:17:50,319
Of course I do.

240
00:17:50,402 --> 00:17:51,570
So where have you been?

241
00:17:52,488 --> 00:17:54,406
Right there. That's what you're good at.

242
00:17:57,534 --> 00:17:58,368
[woman] Hmm.

243
00:17:58,452 --> 00:18:01,080
I know why you are here.

244
00:18:01,705 --> 00:18:03,916
You had to battle it out again
in your mission,

245
00:18:03,999 --> 00:18:06,210
and now you come to me
just to prove you are safe.

246
00:18:06,293 --> 00:18:08,087
Ma, look at me.

247
00:18:09,004 --> 00:18:10,756
I'm still in one piece. See?

248
00:18:11,256 --> 00:18:12,758
Just a few scratches.

249
00:18:13,383 --> 00:18:14,843
I'm fine, Ma.

250
00:18:15,719 --> 00:18:18,180
I know you are good at what you do.

251
00:18:18,263 --> 00:18:20,808
You can to take care
of yourself. But, of course…

252
00:18:22,226 --> 00:18:24,728
I cannot help but worry.

253
00:18:24,812 --> 00:18:27,356
I have already lost a child.

254
00:18:28,607 --> 00:18:30,317
[soft music playing]

255
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:31,235
Ma.

256
00:18:32,820 --> 00:18:34,238
Don't worry.

257
00:18:34,321 --> 00:18:36,240
I'm being careful.

258
00:18:36,865 --> 00:18:39,493
I can handle myself.
Nothing's going to happen to me.

259
00:18:41,912 --> 00:18:44,123
[breathes deeply]

260
00:18:44,206 --> 00:18:45,833
If you'd only seen me earlier, Ma.

261
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:47,501
I was soaring on a motorcycle.

262
00:18:47,584 --> 00:18:49,878
It felt so, so good.

263
00:18:50,462 --> 00:18:51,547
But it wasn't--

264
00:18:51,630 --> 00:18:54,550
- I don't want to ask about it.
- It was a calculated landing.

265
00:18:54,633 --> 00:18:56,426
Wait a second. Why do you smell like fish?

266
00:18:57,136 --> 00:18:58,178
[sniffs]

267
00:18:59,221 --> 00:19:01,181
I was at a public market.

268
00:19:01,849 --> 00:19:03,225
You reek of fish.

269
00:19:03,308 --> 00:19:04,893
- Go take a bath.
- [chuckles]

270
00:19:05,477 --> 00:19:08,313
We should eat first.
Come on, I know you're hungry.

271
00:19:08,397 --> 00:19:11,483
Dig in, Ma. It's your favorite.

272
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:13,193
- Yes. You should eat, too.
- [chuckles softly]

273
00:19:14,361 --> 00:19:16,321
[city noise]

274
00:19:16,405 --> 00:19:21,160
♪ <i>And then out popped</i>
<i>Some hairy legs…</i> ♪

275
00:19:21,243 --> 00:19:23,871
Seriously, man. You missed out big time.

276
00:19:23,954 --> 00:19:26,582
I know, but a family emergency came up.

277
00:19:26,665 --> 00:19:28,250
No, no. We understand.

278
00:19:28,333 --> 00:19:31,461
But you should've seen
Sir Marcus's gun tricks.

279
00:19:31,545 --> 00:19:33,005
- It was insane, dude!
- [man] Yeah!

280
00:19:33,088 --> 00:19:34,173
Only he can pull them off.

281
00:19:34,256 --> 00:19:35,299
He was like a stuntman.

282
00:19:35,382 --> 00:19:36,967
Like an action star in his own movie.

283
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:39,386
Good grief! I'm the topic tonight, huh?

284
00:19:39,469 --> 00:19:40,596
[laughter]

285
00:19:40,679 --> 00:19:42,472
Deal with it, sir.

286
00:19:42,556 --> 00:19:44,349
When you're late,
you're bound to be the topic.

287
00:19:44,433 --> 00:19:45,851
- Yeah!
- Exactly!

288
00:19:45,934 --> 00:19:47,227
- You should've been here earlier!
- [Felix] You know?

289
00:19:47,311 --> 00:19:48,896
Listen, enough talking.

290
00:19:48,979 --> 00:19:50,939
- Let's get him drunk!
- [men] Yeah!

291
00:19:51,023 --> 00:19:52,524
- Time to drink!
- [Marcus] Cheers!

292
00:19:52,608 --> 00:19:54,484
Let's get him wasted

293
00:19:54,568 --> 00:19:56,695
and see if he can still play
the action star

294
00:19:56,778 --> 00:19:58,238
- at the drinking table.
- [laughter]

295
00:19:58,322 --> 00:19:59,823
- [man] Bottoms up.
- [Felix] Let's test him.

296
00:20:02,576 --> 00:20:08,373
- [singing drunkenly]
- [laughter]

297
00:20:10,918 --> 00:20:14,004
- [singing drunkenly]
- [laughing]

298
00:20:15,172 --> 00:20:16,840
- [man 1] Hello.
- [man 2] Sneaking away again.

299
00:20:17,925 --> 00:20:19,551
[Marcus] Are you still
worried about Oliver?

300
00:20:22,387 --> 00:20:23,639
I don't know, sir.

301
00:20:24,264 --> 00:20:27,601
Every time he walks out the door, I…

302
00:20:27,684 --> 00:20:29,311
feel uneasy.

303
00:20:30,520 --> 00:20:34,900
But… he has so much respect
and trust in you.

304
00:20:35,484 --> 00:20:37,527
He always tells me that…

305
00:20:37,611 --> 00:20:39,571
as long as you're together,

306
00:20:39,655 --> 00:20:41,657
you'll have his back.

307
00:20:42,699 --> 00:20:46,912
And that he can return to us…

308
00:20:46,995 --> 00:20:49,456
safe and sound.

309
00:20:52,209 --> 00:20:55,379
[gentle music playing]

310
00:20:55,462 --> 00:20:56,797
You know…

311
00:20:59,675 --> 00:21:02,552
Risk is part of the job.

312
00:21:03,845 --> 00:21:05,138
But don't worry.

313
00:21:05,764 --> 00:21:07,349
I will do everything…

314
00:21:09,434 --> 00:21:11,853
to make sure he always comes home safe.

315
00:21:13,689 --> 00:21:15,899
[gentle music continues]

316
00:21:23,448 --> 00:21:24,992
- [thunder crackling]
- [waves crashing]

317
00:21:32,082 --> 00:21:32,958
- [alarm clock beeping]
- [gasps]

318
00:21:33,041 --> 00:21:34,459
[panting]

319
00:21:34,543 --> 00:21:37,796
[dark music playing]

320
00:21:53,020 --> 00:21:54,521
What do you mean you don't know anything?

321
00:21:54,604 --> 00:21:56,857
You don't even know your arms supplier?

322
00:21:56,940 --> 00:21:58,233
Let me say this one more time.

323
00:21:58,317 --> 00:21:59,609
I don't know anyone.

324
00:21:59,693 --> 00:22:01,236
What do you want me to do?!

325
00:22:01,737 --> 00:22:02,696
[groans]

326
00:22:02,779 --> 00:22:04,614
[Marcus] Are you messing with me, huh?

327
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:07,617
- [Peklat] Believe me, sir!
- [Marcus] You want to rot in prison?!

328
00:22:07,701 --> 00:22:08,744
[Peklat grunting]

329
00:22:08,827 --> 00:22:11,371
I don't know anyone
in the entire operation!

330
00:22:11,455 --> 00:22:13,540
Except my own men!

331
00:22:13,623 --> 00:22:15,542
[labored breaths]

332
00:22:15,625 --> 00:22:17,544
[gloomy music playing]

333
00:22:17,627 --> 00:22:18,462
[groans]

334
00:22:21,506 --> 00:22:22,674
[fists thud]

335
00:22:26,219 --> 00:22:29,139
They deliver the crates of arms
straight to me,

336
00:22:29,222 --> 00:22:30,515
and I move every last one of them.

337
00:22:30,599 --> 00:22:33,310
Once the stock is gone,
they scoop up the cash

338
00:22:33,393 --> 00:22:35,187
and toss me my cut.

339
00:22:35,270 --> 00:22:37,439
Whenever there's a new shipment,

340
00:22:37,522 --> 00:22:40,734
they call me using different numbers.

341
00:22:40,817 --> 00:22:42,486
I can never call them back.

342
00:22:43,070 --> 00:22:44,780
What you're telling me

343
00:22:44,863 --> 00:22:48,033
is that you've been supplying weapons

344
00:22:48,116 --> 00:22:49,701
for your contact for two years

345
00:22:49,785 --> 00:22:52,370
and you still pretend you know nothing?!

346
00:22:52,454 --> 00:22:55,791
I don't know anything,
and I didn't want to know.

347
00:22:55,874 --> 00:22:57,167
[gloomy music continues]

348
00:22:57,250 --> 00:22:58,710
Because I love my family.

349
00:22:58,794 --> 00:22:59,961
What do you mean?

350
00:23:00,045 --> 00:23:03,548
I've seen how cruel they are.

351
00:23:04,132 --> 00:23:06,426
They won't just come after me.

352
00:23:06,510 --> 00:23:10,472
They'll go after everyone I love, too.

353
00:23:10,555 --> 00:23:12,099
Yes, I'm scared.

354
00:23:12,182 --> 00:23:14,142
I'm scared of going to prison.
I don't want to end up in one.

355
00:23:14,226 --> 00:23:15,519
But those people?

356
00:23:16,228 --> 00:23:18,355
Those people terrify me even more.

357
00:23:19,356 --> 00:23:20,857
[gloomy music continues]

358
00:23:29,866 --> 00:23:31,201
They work clean.

359
00:23:31,284 --> 00:23:33,078
Their operation is systematic.

360
00:23:33,161 --> 00:23:35,205
That's why people at the bottom
don't know anything.

361
00:23:35,288 --> 00:23:38,250
So even if we catch someone,
they won't be useful.

362
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:39,751
Just like Peklat.

363
00:23:41,128 --> 00:23:42,963
[breathes deeply]

364
00:23:43,046 --> 00:23:45,590
This syndicate is vast and powerful, Lara.

365
00:23:46,633 --> 00:23:48,802
[gloomy music continues]

366
00:23:55,934 --> 00:23:58,228
According to NLEA's report,

367
00:24:00,355 --> 00:24:05,777
illegal and smuggled firearms

368
00:24:06,570 --> 00:24:11,408
are being dropped in the sea
near the Zamboanga Peninsula.

369
00:24:12,868 --> 00:24:13,785
[ethnic music playing]

370
00:24:28,717 --> 00:24:32,179
[boy] Come on! We're going to be late!
Hurry! Hurry! Whoo!

371
00:24:32,262 --> 00:24:35,098
Come on! We're going to be late!

372
00:24:35,891 --> 00:24:37,851
Come on! Come on! Hurry!

373
00:24:38,977 --> 00:24:41,563
Where were you kids?

374
00:24:42,272 --> 00:24:44,733
[Jamilah] Careful, kids!
You might get hurt!

375
00:24:44,816 --> 00:24:46,359
[boy] Sister Jamilah! Sister Jamilah!

376
00:24:46,443 --> 00:24:49,988
Sorry, we are late. We helped our father.

377
00:24:50,071 --> 00:24:51,489
It's okay. Come on, sit down.

378
00:24:51,573 --> 00:24:54,576
[girl] You guys are failing
because you're always late!

379
00:24:54,659 --> 00:24:56,745
- Oh my goodness.
- [girl 2] Hey!

380
00:24:56,828 --> 00:25:00,081
- [boy] No!
- [Jamilah] That's enough, kids.

381
00:25:00,165 --> 00:25:04,252
Listen, if you get hurt,

382
00:25:04,336 --> 00:25:06,004
do what Sitti did.

383
00:25:06,087 --> 00:25:10,717
First, clean the wound
with clean water and soap.

384
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:13,720
Then go to me, Sister Jamilah.

385
00:25:13,803 --> 00:25:17,599
I will give you medicine
to avoid infection.

386
00:25:17,682 --> 00:25:19,935
- Okay?
- [in unison] Yes!

387
00:25:20,018 --> 00:25:21,978
[Sitti whimpers]

388
00:25:22,062 --> 00:25:24,022
Sister Jamilah…

389
00:25:25,398 --> 00:25:27,859
- You're being silly!
- [Sitti giggles]

390
00:25:27,943 --> 00:25:30,779
I haven't even started! [laughs]

391
00:25:30,862 --> 00:25:32,447
- You're so silly, Sitti!
- [giggles]

392
00:25:32,530 --> 00:25:35,617
- Aah! Sister Jamilah!
- We're almost done.

393
00:25:36,618 --> 00:25:39,204
And, done! Easy-peasy. [chuckles]

394
00:25:39,287 --> 00:25:41,331
See? That didn't hurt at all!

395
00:25:41,414 --> 00:25:43,333
- I'm all done!
- Oh?

396
00:25:43,416 --> 00:25:46,962
Sitti, you are so mischievous! [chuckles]

397
00:25:47,045 --> 00:25:50,298
But since you were such a brave girl,

398
00:25:50,382 --> 00:25:52,592
- you get a reward!
- Wow!

399
00:25:52,676 --> 00:25:54,636
[in Tausug] Thank you, Sister Jamilah!

400
00:25:54,719 --> 00:25:57,055
[in Tagalog] Come here!

401
00:25:59,307 --> 00:26:01,142
You like the bracelet?

402
00:26:01,768 --> 00:26:02,894
Wow.

403
00:26:02,978 --> 00:26:07,816
Let's tighten it so it won't slip off.

404
00:26:07,899 --> 00:26:09,276
[chuckles softly]

405
00:26:09,359 --> 00:26:10,819
He is their leader.

406
00:26:11,653 --> 00:26:15,490
That is Datu Rahman Abubakar.

407
00:26:15,573 --> 00:26:18,243
He has been working in
a gun smuggling syndicate for decades.

408
00:26:18,326 --> 00:26:21,454
He has perfected a system
to evade investigations.

409
00:26:21,955 --> 00:26:23,290
[system beeping]

410
00:26:23,373 --> 00:26:26,960
[Lara] Recently, our own intel
has pinpointed the exact coordinates

411
00:26:27,043 --> 00:26:31,923
where the contraband is dropped,
picked up, and hidden

412
00:26:32,632 --> 00:26:35,302
prior to being illegally
distributed to warlords,

413
00:26:35,385 --> 00:26:37,554
terrorists, and private individuals.

414
00:26:37,637 --> 00:26:40,849
He is very charismatic,
a natural-born leader,

415
00:26:40,932 --> 00:26:43,685
but also a master manipulator.

416
00:26:44,936 --> 00:26:46,896
He is loved by the people on his island,

417
00:26:46,980 --> 00:26:49,399
and they will defend him with their lives.

418
00:26:49,482 --> 00:26:53,069
Therefore, you cannot coordinate
with the local authorities.

419
00:26:53,153 --> 00:26:55,155
We need to keep
this operation under wraps.

420
00:26:55,739 --> 00:26:57,574
Otherwise, he'll slip
right through your hands.

421
00:26:57,657 --> 00:26:59,576
[stirring music playing]

422
00:27:02,078 --> 00:27:04,456
[woman] They're here!

423
00:27:04,998 --> 00:27:06,291
I hope they brought home a lot of fish.

424
00:27:06,374 --> 00:27:07,334
‪[woman 2] My husband…

425
00:27:08,126 --> 00:27:11,129
- [woman] I think they did!
- [man] Yes!

426
00:27:11,212 --> 00:27:14,215
- [man] Be careful.
- Thank you, thank you. [grunts]

427
00:27:15,800 --> 00:27:17,635
[indistinct chatter]

428
00:27:19,012 --> 00:27:21,473
- [woman] Good thing you caught a lot!
- [man] Here.

429
00:27:21,556 --> 00:27:25,727
- [man] Wow! There's so much!
- [woman] Oh, I hope these have pearls!

430
00:27:25,810 --> 00:27:27,020
Datu Rahman.

431
00:27:27,103 --> 00:27:29,314
- [in Arabic] Peace be with you.
- Peace be with you, too.

432
00:27:29,397 --> 00:27:30,648
[indistinct chattering]

433
00:27:30,732 --> 00:27:34,152
[sinister music]

434
00:27:39,157 --> 00:27:40,867
[in Tagalog] There is
another shipment coming.

435
00:27:40,950 --> 00:27:42,827
[tense music playing]

436
00:27:47,499 --> 00:27:48,833
[Jamilah] Father!

437
00:27:53,963 --> 00:27:54,881
Father.

438
00:27:54,964 --> 00:27:57,133
[in Tausug] How is my daughter?

439
00:27:57,217 --> 00:27:59,844
- [in Tagalog] I'm good, Father.
- [Rahman chuckles]

440
00:28:00,762 --> 00:28:03,765
Datu Rahman Abubakar can lead us

441
00:28:03,848 --> 00:28:08,269
to the head
of the gun smuggling syndicate.

442
00:28:08,353 --> 00:28:11,898
This is the arrest warrant
for Datu Rahman Abubakar.

443
00:28:11,981 --> 00:28:15,068
Men, please proceed with extreme caution.

444
00:28:15,777 --> 00:28:17,987
These people are armed and dangerous.

445
00:28:18,071 --> 00:28:21,491
Whoa! Armed and dangerous?

446
00:28:21,574 --> 00:28:24,160
Why do we still need to arrest them?

447
00:28:24,744 --> 00:28:25,829
They're criminals.

448
00:28:25,912 --> 00:28:28,748
We should just eliminate
these scoundrels--

449
00:28:28,832 --> 00:28:30,417
- Domingo. Domingo.
- [Felix] Am I right?

450
00:28:30,500 --> 00:28:31,876
[Felix scoffs]

451
00:28:31,960 --> 00:28:32,961
Come on.

452
00:28:33,044 --> 00:28:36,714
Our mission is to capture and arrest

453
00:28:37,340 --> 00:28:38,758
Datu Rahman Abubakar.

454
00:28:40,510 --> 00:28:45,682
We will only use force
and weapons when necessary.

455
00:28:47,142 --> 00:28:49,978
We are not going to that island to kill.

456
00:28:51,104 --> 00:28:52,272
Is that clear?

457
00:28:52,355 --> 00:28:53,440
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

458
00:28:56,443 --> 00:28:57,652
Domingo.

459
00:28:58,695 --> 00:28:59,654
Sir.

460
00:29:00,321 --> 00:29:01,364
Yes, sir.

461
00:29:02,657 --> 00:29:03,616
[chuckles]

462
00:29:03,700 --> 00:29:05,618
[tense music playing]

463
00:29:22,552 --> 00:29:26,264
[suspenseful music playing]

464
00:29:28,975 --> 00:29:30,935
[man] Datu Rahman, they're all tied up.

465
00:29:32,103 --> 00:29:33,146
Okay.

466
00:29:33,229 --> 00:29:34,147
Come on. Come on.

467
00:29:34,230 --> 00:29:35,523
- Get in.
- [man] Okay.

468
00:29:36,107 --> 00:29:38,359
[suspenseful music continues]

469
00:29:45,992 --> 00:29:47,619
[suspenseful music continues]

470
00:30:08,723 --> 00:30:10,517
[Jamilah] <i>We are a family here.</i>

471
00:30:10,600 --> 00:30:13,895
[Jalil] <i>No matter what happens,</i>
<i>I will always come home.</i>

472
00:30:13,978 --> 00:30:16,022
[Rahman] <i>I have something to show you.</i>

473
00:30:16,105 --> 00:30:19,442
[Lara] <i>Capturing Datu Rahman</i>
<i>will be vital in our investigation.</i>

474
00:30:19,526 --> 00:30:21,528
If I don't piss off any bad guys,

475
00:30:21,611 --> 00:30:23,780
<i>it means I'm not doing my job correctly.</i>

476
00:30:23,863 --> 00:30:28,368
The syndicate is still delivering weapons.

477
00:30:28,451 --> 00:30:30,328
[Jalil] <i>Let's surrender these</i>
<i>to the police.</i>

478
00:30:30,411 --> 00:30:32,121
[Marcus] <i>We need to succeed, Lara.</i>

479
00:30:32,205 --> 00:30:34,958
[Lara] <i>This is just the beginning</i>
<i>of Task Force Alpha's mission.</i>

480
00:30:35,041 --> 00:30:37,752
[indistinct chatter, laughter]

481
00:30:39,128 --> 00:30:41,005
[dramatic music]

482
00:30:42,799 --> 00:30:45,260
- [screaming]
- [gunshots]
